{"key":"post-12725141","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>12725141</id>\n<content>A fan won't push air through a filter.&amp;nbsp; It will cavitate and you'll get nothing.&amp;nbsp; You need a squirrel cage blower.&amp;nbsp; Your plenum behind the filter needs to be as large as the filter itself. A pressurized plenum is the way you get the exact same amount of pressure on the entire back side, ensuring laminar flow out the front side.&amp;nbsp; Build a plywood box to house the filter if you want to go cheap, or use hardwood planed planks glued together if you're a woodworker and want to build a piece of furniture you can be proud of.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Search here for flowhood plans.&amp;nbsp; I've typed the calculations to determine the blower size in CFM @ 1&quot; static pressure for a 2 X 4 blower so many times that it's not necessary to repeat them all again.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>12725165</next>\n<prev>12725130</prev>\n<first>12721845</first>\n<last>12762817</last>\n<when>1276267034</when>\n<utime>06/11/10 05:37 PM</utime>\n</post>"}